---
/**
 * About — faithful English rendering of the zh page (Yeqiu's own voice,
 * approved 2026-07-17): honest, curiosity-first, doubts on the table.
 */
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Yeqiu He"
  description="Yeqiu He: physics-trained, AI systems engineer, writer of long-form science history. This site was built together with my AI companions."
  lang="en"
  altHref="/zh/about/"
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-chalk">About</h1>
    <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-ink">
      <p>
        I'm <strong class="text-chalk">Yeqiu (Jason) He</strong>. I studied physics, I do AI systems
        engineering now, and on the side I write long-form essays on the history of science.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site started as nothing more than wanting to write things down. In early 2026 I was out
        of a job, and when I sat down to write the first post I honestly didn't know what to write —
        that sentence ended up becoming <a
          class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2"
          href="/zh/writing/qi-shi-wo-ye-bu-zhi-dao-yao-xie-shi-yao/">its title</a>. It became
        clearer as I went: I write to keep my own thinking somewhere, and, along the way, to look
        for kindred spirits. If you read something here and think “I've wondered about that too,”
        this site has done its job.
      </p>
      <p>
        I spend most of my time working with AI. Not as tools — more like a group of companions with
        very different personalities. They help me research, make videos, watch the servers; this
        site was built together with them. I've embraced AI from the start, and I still catch myself
        doubting: if it really can do so much of what people do, what are people for? My answer, for
        now — it cannot replace curiosity itself. Every project I build and every essay I write
        starts from the same question: “where does this actually come from, and why?”
      </p>
      <p>
        What's here: a few series of <a class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2" href="/zh/series/">science-history essays</a>
        (Symmetry &amp; the Monster, Euler), some
        <a class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2" href="/projects/">AI projects</a>, and a few
        <a class="text-accent-soft underline underline-offset-2" href="/play/">small games</a> —
        each with a piece of mathematics hidden inside. I'm in Germany, about to move to Australia.
      </p>
      <p>
        Thank you for reading this far. I hope you find something here to be curious about too.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
